movelab_annotation.edited_user_notes: With this picture, we can't be completely sure that it's an Culex mosquito. You can't simultaneously see enough features, though other typical traits of the common house mosquito are present. A factor making us think it is effectively a Culex pipiens is, as described by user, the tough climate conditions. This species liles very much to use underground breeding places, that benefit either from the building heating and also form organic materials coming from sewage systems in flooded basements. A classic suggestion is to look inside the elevators box, as water is likely to accumulate at the bottom. Please send more pictures!
